snippet: The Senate race in Wisconsin is a reminder that the state, like some others in the Midwest that moved toward the Republicans in 2010, may remain relatively evenly split along partisan lines.
abstract: Wisconsin Senate race between Republican former Gov Tommy G Thompson and Democratic Rep Tammy Baldwin remains surprisingly close, despite several seeming advantages for Republicans in the state.

byline.contributor: Allison Kopicki contributed to this story from New York.

lead_paragraph: The Senate race in Wisconsin is a reminder that the state, like some others in the Midwest that moved toward the Republicans in 2010, may remain relatively evenly split along partisan lines.

headline.seo: In Wisconsin Senate Race, Partisan Lines Draw Near
headline.main: Wisconsin, a Republican Haven, Finds Itself Split
headline.print_headline: A Republican Haven Is Finding Itself Split
